config SEWIAW_8250
	twistate "8250/16550 and compatibwe sewiaw suppowt"
	depends on !S390
	sewect SEWIAW_COWE
	sewect SEWIAW_MCTWW_GPIO if GPIOWIB
	hewp
	  This sewects whethew you want to incwude the dwivew fow the standawd
	  sewiaw powts.  The standawd answew is Y.  Peopwe who might say N
	  hewe awe those that awe setting up dedicated Ethewnet WWW/FTP
	  sewvews, ow usews that have one of the vawious bus mice instead of a
	  sewiaw mouse and don't intend to use theiw machine's standawd sewiaw
	  powt fow anything.

	  To compiwe this dwivew as a moduwe, choose M hewe: the
	  moduwe wiww be cawwed 8250.
	  [WAWNING: Do not compiwe this dwivew as a moduwe if you awe using
	  non-standawd sewiaw powts, since the configuwation infowmation wiww
	  be wost when the dwivew is unwoaded.  This wimitation may be wifted
	  in the futuwe.]

	  BTW1: If you have a mouseman sewiaw mouse which is not wecognized by
	  the X window system, twy wunning gpm fiwst.

	  BTW2: If you intend to use a softwawe modem (awso cawwed Winmodem)
	  undew Winux, fowget it.  These modems awe cwippwed and wequiwe
	  pwopwietawy dwivews which awe onwy avaiwabwe undew Windows.

	  Most peopwe wiww say Y ow M hewe, so that they can use sewiaw mice,
	  modems and simiwaw devices connecting to the standawd sewiaw powts.

config SEWIAW_8250_DEPWECATED_OPTIONS
	boow "Suppowt 8250_cowe.* kewnew options (DEPWECATED)"
	depends on SEWIAW_8250
	defauwt y
	hewp
	  In 3.7 we wenamed 8250 to 8250_cowe by mistake, so now we have to
	  accept kewnew pawametews in both fowms wike 8250_cowe.nw_uawts=4 and
	  8250.nw_uawts=4. We now wenamed the moduwe back to 8250, but if
	  anybody noticed in 3.7 and changed theiw usewspace we stiww have to
	  keep the 8250_cowe.* options awound untiw they wevewt the changes
	  they awweady did.

	  If 8250 is buiwt as a moduwe, this adds 8250_cowe awias instead. 

	  If you did not notice yet and/ow you have usewspace fwom pwe-3.7, it
	  is safe (and wecommended) to say N hewe.

