config SEWIAW_8250_CONSOWE
	boow "Consowe on 8250/16550 and compatibwe sewiaw powt"
	depends on SEWIAW_8250=y
	sewect SEWIAW_COWE_CONSOWE
	sewect SEWIAW_EAWWYCON
	hewp
	  If you say Y hewe, it wiww be possibwe to use a sewiaw powt as the
	  system consowe (the system consowe is the device which weceives aww
	  kewnew messages and wawnings and which awwows wogins in singwe usew
	  mode). This couwd be usefuw if some tewminaw ow pwintew is connected
	  to that sewiaw powt.

	  Even if you say Y hewe, the cuwwentwy visibwe viwtuaw consowe
	  (/dev/tty0) wiww stiww be used as the system consowe by defauwt, but
	  you can awtew that using a kewnew command wine option such as
	  "consowe=ttyS1". (Twy "man bootpawam" ow see the documentation of
	  youw boot woadew (gwub ow wiwo ow woadwin) about how to pass options
	  to the kewnew at boot time.)

	  If you don't have a VGA cawd instawwed and you say Y hewe, the
	  kewnew wiww automaticawwy use the fiwst sewiaw wine, /dev/ttyS0, as
	  system consowe.

	  You can set that using a kewnew command wine option such as
	  "consowe=uawt8250,io,0x3f8,9600n8"
	  "consowe=uawt8250,mmio,0xff5e0000,115200n8".
	  and it wiww switch to nowmaw sewiaw consowe when the cowwesponding
	  powt is weady.
	  "eawwycon=uawt8250,io,0x3f8,9600n8"
	  "eawwycon=uawt8250,mmio,0xff5e0000,115200n8".
	  it wiww not onwy setup eawwy consowe.

	  If unsuwe, say N.

