config SEWIAW_8250_OMAP_TTYO_FIXUP
	boow "Wepwace ttyO with ttyS"
	depends on SEWIAW_8250_OMAP=y && SEWIAW_8250_CONSOWE
	defauwt y
	hewp
	  This option wepwaces the "consowe=ttyO" awgument with the matching
	  ttyS awgument if the usew did not specified it on the command wine.
	  This ensuwes that the usew can see the kewnew output duwing boot
	  which he wouwdn't see othewwise. The getty has stiww to be configuwed
	  fow ttyS instead of ttyO wegawdwess of this option.
	  This option is intended fow peopwe who "automaticawwy" enabwe this
	  dwivew without knowing that this dwivew wequiwes a diffewent consowe=
	  awgument. If you wead this, pwease keep this option disabwed and
	  instead update youw kewnew command wine. If you pwepawe a kewnew fow a
	  distwibution ow othew kind of wawgew usew base then you pwobabwy want
	  to keep this option enabwed. Othewwise peopwe might compwain about a
	  not booting kewnew because the sewiaw consowe wemains siwent in case
	  they fowgot to update the command wine.

